		"Name": "Roughneck",
		"Details": "A militarized BattleMech version of Achernar's Loader King IndustrialMech, the Roughneck is a low-cost heavy 'Mech intended for price-conscious buyers such as planetary militias and down-on-their-luck mercenary units. The Taurian Concordat, after their recent fighting and later treaty with the Sanctuary Alliance, rolled out this 'Drone' cockpit RGH-1ATL testbed based on the Roughneck RGH-1B.  No We don't know why it is designated 1ATL if it is based on the 1B either!  First, upgrading the Autocannon to an Ultra Autocannon-10 type with 3 tons of CASE2-protected ammunition was achieved.  The SRM and Machinegun ammunition were then moved to the same CASE2-protected location as the UAC/10 ammunition.   All other weapons remain the same as on the donor chassis, the RGH-1B.  However, the extra mass of the CASE2, as well as the denser 325 core and the UAC/10, had to be accounted for.  This accounting took form in dual style heatsinks to make this a heat-viable combat unit, and the XL shielding for the 325 fusion core.  The cost went up significantly, but it is still cheaper than a new Thunderbolt Mech!   This mech was upgraded by Pafftek Industries in conjunction with Achernarâ€™s ability to provide new sub-assemblies for various locations on the mech.",
